2026-04-16 07:54:47 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 1', 'Control module 2', 'Control module 3', 'Control module 4', 'Control module 5', 'Control module 6', 'Control module 7', 'Control module 8'] hypothesis_explanation='The observation confirms that all indicator LEDs (acting as switch indicators) in control modules 1 to 8 have been removed. In this circuit design, the indicator LED and its series resistor provide a path for current to flow when the corresponding switch is closed. With the LEDs physically absent, the circuit path in each control module is open even with all switches on, interrupting current flow through the entire circuit including the load module, so the main lamp cannot turn on. The root cause is the missing indicator LEDs in the control modules.'
